info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 13 at 5:55PM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir affecting Wood County. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS AFTERNOON UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir. * WHEN...From this afternoon until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 1017.0 feet, Widespread wooded lowland flooding. Water approaches a few homes on South Biron Drive in Biron. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 4:10 PM CDT Wednesday the stage was 1017.3 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 4:10 PM CDT Wednesday was 1017.3 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1017.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 1017.3 feet on 12/16/2015. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Thursday afternoon.
